abstract: A dispatch from Houston, Texas, reports an unprecedented flood in the Colorado Valley. abstract: Four of the children of Mr. JAMES WILMOT, who resides near Valley City, Harrison County, were burned to death on Saturday night June 26. abstract: The reports that the Secretary of the Navy has declared that he will do nothing about the names given by Ex-Secretary BORIE to certain of our vessels are unfounded. He has expressed no such determination, and there is reason to believe that, at his own time and in his own way, he will take satisfactory action.

abstract: Efforts are making in England to facilitate the exportation of cotton from India, as the supply from the United States is not equal to the demand. The Cotton Supply Association, of Liverpool, have just adopted a resolution looking to the speedy development of railroads in India, to this end.

abstract: At a late hour last evening a difficulty occurred in front of No. 55 Mulberry-street between DENNIS CONNORS, who resides in the house, and MICHAEL McCABE, of No. 69 Oliver-street. McCABE striking CONNORS with his fist, the latter drew a knife, and, making a large at McCABE, inflicted a severe, but not necessarily dangerous stab wound in his neck.
